title: DC Women's Cyclocross Camp
description: One day women's cyclocross clinic in Washignton DC.
registration:
Join Fearless Femme racing team, Fulcrum Coaching, and In The Crosshairs for a Women’s only cyclocross clinic at the Armed Forces Retirement Home in Washington DC

Cyclocross racing not only requires you to be in great physical shape but also relies on a unique skill set.  Learning and mastering these skills will make you a better racer this cyclocross season.
Attendees will learn:
•	Dismounting
•	Remounting
•	Carrying/Shouldering
•	Off-Cambers
•	Cornering
•	Starts
•	Clipping in quickly
•	The anatomy of a race course
•	Equipment and tire selection
•	Race course evaluation
•	1 lap practice race

On site mechanical support will be provided. The course and grounds will be professionally groomed for the clinic.

We will have 4 coaches (Arley Kemmerer, Rachel Rubino, Dan Tille, and Rusty Williford) in attendance to ensure each attendee gets plenty of individual instruction.

Cross Clinic cost: $ 150
Cross Camp attendee current limit: 40
The Clinic is held rain or shine but will be canceled if there are thunderstorms.

In addition to learning valuable cyclocross skills from some of the top female professionals in cyclocross and our other coaches, lunch, drinks and snacks will be provided.
Campers will need a current USA Cycling License to participate. One-day licenses ($10) will be available for purchase at registration.
